  "text": "Of the human immunoglobulin classes IgG, IgA, IgM, and IgD, only IgG binds to HSV type 1-(HSV-1) infected cells in a nonimmune manner [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We have recently described that of the four human IgG subclasses IgG3 does not bind to HSV-1-infected cells, whereas the binding of the remaining subclasses differs according to the sequence IgG4 > IgG1-IgG2 [CITATION_3] .",
